Harlequins have announced that fly-half Tim Swiel will return to the club next season on a full-time contract . Swiel , 21 , spent four months on loan with Quins earlier this term before heading back to the Durban-based Sharks in South Africa . ` Tim made a real impact with us on loan earlier in the season and we are delighted that the Sharks have granted him his release to come back to us on a full-time basis , ' Quins rugby director Conor O'Shea said . Tim Swiel will return to H . ` He is a young player with a huge amount of potential and also someone who showed mentally that he is able to cope with anything thrown at him . ' Somerset-born Swiel made 10 appearances during his loan spell , featuring in the European Champions Cup , Aviva Premiership and LV = Cup .